sentences.en: We have sufficient supplies to last the winter.
sentences.zh: 我们有足够的供应来度过冬天。

sentences.en: She was unaware of the danger.
He traveled incognito to avoid the press.
sentences.zh: 他隐姓埋名地旅行以避开媒体。

sentences.en: She was a prominent member of the community.

means.en: all the visible features of an area of land

sentences.en: The landscape was dotted with small villages.

means.en: to stop and catch something or someone before that thing or person is able to reach a particular place

sentences.en: The police intercepted the stolen vehicle as it was leaving the city.
sentences.zh: 警方在被盗车辆离开城市时将其拦截下来。

sentences.en: She failed her driving test on the first attempt.
sentences.zh: 她第一次尝试驾照考试就失败了。

means.en: having good judgment and the ability to act correctly and make decisions on your own

sentences.zh: 他是一个非常负责任的人。

means.en: the act of connecting electrical wires

sentences.en: The technician is wiring up the new network.
sentences.zh: 技术人员正在接新网络的线。

means.en: to change something slightly, especially in order to make it more correct

sentences.en: He tweaked the settings of the computer program.
sentences.zh: 他微调了计算机程序的设置。

sentences.en: Proceed with caution when driving in the rain.
sentences.zh: 在雨中驾驶时要小心行事。

sentences.en: The report contains some inaccurate information.
sentences.zh: 这份报告包含一些不准确的信息。

means.en: stored or recorded for future use

sentences.en: The archived documents were stored in a secure location.
sentences.zh: 存档的文档被储存在一个安全的地点。

means.en: a formal address or discourse delivered to an audience

sentences.en: The President gave a speech about the state of the union.
sentences.zh: 总统就联邦的状况发表了演讲。
